This paper discusses plan modification in conformant planning problems, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning (cs.PL). The paper also uses quantitative analysis and experiments, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the separation of regions based on a threshold, which is a concept often used in control systems (cs.SY).
